Here&#39;s a function `adder`. It allows you to create new adding functions.

It accepts an argument `a` and returns a new function. The returned function (a closure - a function that has access to its outer lexical environment) accepts an argument `b` and - _when it is called_ - returns the sum of `a` and `b`. 

We assign the result of calling `adder` (which is a function) to `addTwo`. We then call `addTwo` with an argument (`b`) which returns the value of `a + b`.

